article.description: Trevor Stumpe scored 14 of his 18 points in the second half to help seventh-seeded Wofford pull away to eliminate No. 2 seed Furman 77-68 in a Southern Conference tournament quarterfinal on Saturday.
article.headline: Wofford upsets Furman 77-68 in SoCon tourney quarterfinal
article.linkText: Wofford upsets Furman 77-68 in SoCon tourney quarterfinal
article.story: ASHEVILLE, N.C. -- Trevor Stumpe scored 14 of his 18 points in the second half to help seventh-seeded Wofford pull away to eliminate No. 2 seed Furman 77-68 in a Southern Conference tournament quarterfinal on Saturday. Wofford (18-15) will play sixth-seeded Chattanooga (20-12) in a Sunday semifinal. Chevez Goodwin scored 19 points to lead the Terriers. Storm Murphy added 15 points. Mike Bothwell scored 18 points for Furman (25-7). Jordan Lyons added 15 points and Clay Mounce had 13. as Wofford built its largest lead of the game, Furman cut the deficit to 68-62 with 3:04 to play, but Wofford answered with a 6-0 surge for another 12-point lead with 28 seconds left. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25
